---

## Express API Codebase - Complete Analysis

### 1. **PROJECT STRUCTURE**

```
├── src/
│   ├── app.ts                 # Main Express app configuration
│   ├── server.ts              # Server entry point
│   ├── db.ts                  # In-memory database with seed data
│   ├── types.ts               # TypeScript interface definitions
│   └── middleware/
│       └── logger.ts          # Request logging middleware
│   └── routes/
│       ├── posts.ts           # Posts endpoints
│       └── comments.ts        # Comments endpoints
├── tests/
│   ├── posts.test.ts          # Posts route tests
│   ├── comments.test.ts       # Comments route tests
│   └── auth.test.ts           # Authentication & authorization tests
├── package.json               # Project metadata and dependencies
├── tsconfig.json              # TypeScript configuration
└── .gitignore                 # Git ignore rules
```

---

### 2. **MAIN ENTRY POINT - src/server.ts**

```typescript
import { app } from "./app.js";

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;

app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});

export { app };
```

Starts an Express server on port 3000 (or custom PORT env var).

---

